OL,3,CHas this been the UK's wettest winter?
OL,4,CWhat the data shows
OL,6,FClimate change is also impacting our
OL,7,Frainfall.
OL,9,FFor every degree Celsius increase in
OL,10,Ftemperature, the atmosphere can hold
OL,11,F7% more moisture.
OL,13,FA warmer atmosphere means more water
OL,14,Fcan be held, leading to more intense
OL,15,Frainfall.
OL,17,FOur winters are therefore getting
OL,18,Fwetter due to climate change, which
OL,19,Fmeans when we do get rain, it is
OL,20,Fheavier and lasts longer than before.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G8/11
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
