PN,30711
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F307A1772197440
OL,3,CHas this been the UK's wettest winter?
OL,4,CWhat the data shows
OL,6,FMet Office Senior Scientist Mike
OL,7,FKendon said: "Although the past week
OL,8,Fhas been more settled, it looks like
OL,9,Fthis winter will close a very wet one
OL,10,Ffor parts of southern England,
OL,11,Fremembered for its relentless rain as
OL,12,Fmuch as its intensity."
OL,14,FOn Monday, we will have a more
OL,15,Faccurate idea of the UK's winter
OL,16,Fweather, but it's clear to see that
OL,17,Fit's certainly felt wetter and less
OL,18,Fsunny than usual.
OL,20,FAnd as the climate becomes warmer, we
OL,21,Fshould expect more wet winters to come.
